From: doujialong <doujialong@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: dts: sun8i-h3-nanopi-m1-plus: switch EMAC to rgmii-id

The NanoPi M1 Plus ships a Realtek RTL8211E PHY wired to the Allwinner
H3 EMAC via RGMII.  On the current device tree the EMAC is declared as
"rgmii", which leaves the clock-delay up to the PHY.  The RTL8211E on
this board does not have its internal delay enabled by default, so the
link comes up (LEDs blink, auto-negotiation reports 1000BASE-T full
duplex), but no packets can actually flow through the MAC: outgoing
frames get dropped and ping shows 100% packet loss.

Switch the EMAC phy-mode to "rgmii-id" so the Linux kernel asks the
PHY to add RX and TX clock delays internally.  This matches what
DietPi / mainline U-Boot do on this board and restores working
gigabit Ethernet on OpenWrt / ImmortalWRT.

Reported-by: NanoPi M1 Plus owners
Signed-off-by: doujialong <doujialong@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3-nanopi-m1-plus.dts | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3-nanopi-m1-plus.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3-nanopi-m1-plus.dts
@@ -90,7 +90,7 @@
 	pinctrl-0 = <&emac_rgmii_pins>;
 	phy-supply = <&reg_gmac_3v3>;
 	phy-handle = <&ext_rgmii_phy>;
-	phy-mode = "rgmii";
+	phy-mode = "rgmii-id";
 
 	status = "okay";
 };
